# AI-Controlled Component Features

Our system provides comprehensive AI control over component styling and behavior through various control sets. Below is a detailed breakdown of all available features.

## 1. Background Controls
Control component background appearance:
- Background color (any valid CSS color)
- Background image (URL or data URL)
- Background image removal
- Transparency/opacity
- Combined color and image effects

## 2. Border Controls
Manage component borders and shadows:
- Border width (all sides or individual)
- Border style (solid, dashed, dotted, etc.)
- Border color
- Border radius (all corners or individual)
- Inner shadows
- Outer shadows
- Border presets

## 3. Spacing Controls
Handle component spacing:
- Padding (all sides or individual)
- Margin (all sides or individual)
- Gap between flex items
- Spacing presets:
  - Small (8px)
  - Medium (16px)
  - Large (24px)
- Auto margins for centering

## 4. Size Controls
Manage component dimensions:
- Width and height
- Minimum/maximum constraints
- Aspect ratio
- Fit content options
- Size presets:
  - Square (equal width/height)
  - Banner (full width, fixed height)
  - Card (fixed width, auto height)
  - Full (100% width/height)
- Responsive sizing (%, vw, vh)
- Calc expressions support

## 5. Layout Controls
Control flex container behavior:
- Display type (flex, block, etc.)
- Flex direction (row, column)
- Flex wrap
- Justify content
- Align items
- Align content
- Child element properties:
  - Flex grow/shrink
  - Flex basis
  - Order
- Layout presets:
  - Row layout
  - Column layout
  - Grid-like layout
  - Centered layout
  - Space between

## 6. Button Controls
Manage button interactions:
- Hover effects:
  - Background color change
  - Text color change
  - Scale transform
- Cursor styles
- Transition effects:
  - Duration
  - Timing function
- Page navigation:
  - Enable/disable
  - Target page selection
- Hover presets:
  - Subtle
  - Medium
  - Strong

## Valid Units
- Absolute: px, em, rem
- Relative: %, vw, vh
- Special: auto, fit-content
- Time: ms (milliseconds)

## Color Formats
- Hexadecimal: #RGB, #RGBA, #RRGGBB, #RRGGBBAA
- RGB: rgb(r,g,b), rgba(r,g,b,a)
- HSL: hsl(h,s,l), hsla(h,s,l,a)
- Named colors: red, blue, transparent, etc.

## Best Practices
1. Use relative units (%, vw, vh) for responsive designs
2. Implement consistent spacing using the preset values
3. Consider mobile views when setting minimum/maximum constraints
4. Use transition effects for smooth interactions
5. Ensure sufficient color contrast for accessibility
6. Test hover effects on both desktop and mobile devices

## Limitations
- Some complex CSS properties may require direct code modification
- Background images must be provided as URLs
- Custom timing functions for transitions need specific syntax
- Some advanced flexbox features may require manual configuration